<br>
Yesterday I go to see Kandin. He was apprehensive, answers as intended when I hail him, but keep the Green Oil without giving anything to me. Until now I have done all parts of the Epic quest without using any tricks, but it's not sufficient to avoid faction problems <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
So I have petitionned and less than 2 hours later a GM-Admin give me the Staff and the Note. The GM says that <br>
when I will have collected the last staff (Phiny's staff) I will have to petition for assistance to complete my epic because the turn-in with Arantir will not work either.<br>
<br>
I have asked if there are some way to increase my faction by doing a few parts of another Epic quest like shaman quest with the lesser spirit, and the GM have answered that does not works in this case.<br>
<br>
1/ Does anyone have recently (very important) used the &quot;lesser spirit&quot; quest to improve True Spirit faction and do successful turn-in with Arantir (and then Solomen) after an unsuccessful turn-in with Kandin just like me ?<br>
<br>
<br>
Some people seem to have successfully used the invis tricks for all turn-in, even with a MQ (I have seen message from HappyWIzard and JakXev). On the other hand, some people recommend to not use invis trick (I have seen a answer from Caldaer &quot;And don't try to do the invis trade trick either&quot;). And I have heard rumors about invis trick not possible anymore, MQ not possible anymore and so on.<br>
<br>
2/ Does anyone have recently (very important) used successfully the invis trick for a normal turn-in and/or a MQ turn-in with Arantir (and then Solomen) ? Do you know someone who recently *failed* using this trick ?<br>
<br>
I would appreciate to have recent information, because after each patch something new could have been broken (like the golem <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   !)<br>
<br>
Edit: I forgot to give my personnal trick for a very quick &quot;lesser spirit&quot; loop quest (I have done this to help for a SK epic). Bind you near the NPC in Freeport (he has 2 spots, but they are near from each other) where a friend wait to invis you when needed. Take a Cleric with you at your &quot;lesser spirit&quot; spot. Ask the Barde or Chanter to keep the &quot;lesser spirit&quot; charmed. Duel someone. Ask a rezz. And then the loop begin :<br>
- Do the lesser spirit dialog<br>
- Gate<br>
- Give the stone with invis trick (if needed) to the NPC<br>
- Ask a rez (the basic rez, with no xp back)<br>
- Do the lesser spirit dialog.<br>
- ...<br>
<br>
Don't take any risk with the &quot;corpse too old&quot; (something like 7 min for a duel death) : loot, duel again to let a new fresh corpse before the time limit.<br>
<br>
If you zone fast in Freeport and let say Butcherblock, this is a very effective way to gain True Spirit faction hit. You can do the quest 7 times in a row.<br>
<br>
